<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<%- include('partials/header'); %>

    <body>
       

        <%- include('partials/nav'); %>
            <!--Partial of nav-->
            <section>
                <h2 class="faq">FAQ</h2>
                <h3>How Do I create a file for submission</h3>
                <p>
                    As this project is in its prelimiary stages, any submission file will be a text file.
                    <br> Unsure how to create a text file?

                <ol id="more">
                    <li>Copy the entire email thread with command CTRL-C on your keyboard</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>For Windows users: Right Click on your Desktop and hover to the new selection for Text
                            Document</li>
                        <li>For Mac: Open TextEdit and create a plain text file </li>
                    </ul>
                    <li>Paste contents with CTRL-V. Make sure all the thread was included for best accuracy </li>
                    <li>Save the text file under any name. For Mac users, make sure the file is txt and not rtf </li>
                </ol>

                <!--The instruction will be revealed by the button-->
                <!--JS adds functionality to drop down button-->
                </p>
                <button id="btn" class="button">See More</button>


                <h3>What information can I acesss once I log in ?</h3>
                <p>
                    The Adminstrator of your group threads:
                <ul>
                    <li>The master transcript of the analyzed email thread</li>
                    <li>Your 1:1 chats with other memembers</li>
                    <li>The original copy of the submission file </li>
                    <li>Ability to delete the threads from the database</li>
                </ul>
                As non-admin users:
                <ul>
                    <li>The analyzed group chat that the user is CC'D in</li>
                    <li>Any 1:1: messages with any group memebers in the submission file</li>
                </ul>
                </p>

                <h3>I submitted my file and the browser received a error, What happen?</h3>
                <p>
                    The transimission from the webpage to the analysis program failed. This may be from: submission
                    file's type,
                    the current network is unstable, and etc.
                    Please pay attention to the error message given and retry submission.
                </p>

            </section>
            <!--This section gives quick rundown on what file forced download on their -->
            <!--javascript required-->
            <script>
                /*Javascript for Esum
                 Created by Vyanna Hill
                 Usage is for the log in "page" of Esum
                */
                var visText = document.getElementById("more");
                var button = document.getElementById("btn");
                visText.style.display = "none";
                //We set the instructions to invisible

                button.addEventListener("click", function () {
                    if (button.innerHTML == "See More") {
                        visText.style.display = "inline";
                        button.innerHTML = "See Less";
                    } else {
                        visText.style.display = "none";
                        button.innerHTML = "See More";
                    }
                    //When User clicks button the first time, Instructions are revealed and button rewritten to See less
                    //When the User want to hide them again, the click will hide them and See More appears on the button again
                });

            </script>
            <!--uses external Javascript -->
    </body>

